title: What I Should Have Said
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Aqu8y9

by WilmaKins

Ever since Siberia, Steve has been thinking of Tony. All those things he was so scared to tell him…

And, in the end, it was what he didn’t tell him that ruined them.

OR

Steve Rogers reflects on all the times he should have just told Tony what he was thinking.

summary: i really think a lot about that part in venom with the bike and cars chase, especially that one scene where venom protected...
body:
i really think a lot about that part in venom with the bike and cars chase, especially that one scene where venom protected eddie from a collision with one car and eddie said ‘thank you” and venom replied “you’re welcome’. (i’m crying here thinking about how many times did venom ever hear the phrase ‘thank you’ probably not much before eddie)

and also despite that chase being dangerous, right at the end of it eddie was smiling, maybe for the first time since his break up with anne? at least what we saw. like he genuinely seemed to enjoy this stupid dangerous chase while his body was being invaded by an alien symbiote. incredible
